data.name: Cancel the Job
reason_code
data.description: The reason code to cancel the job; Possible values are: 67 - Accidental opening creation 51 - All positions filled  49 - Filled by alternate source  41 - Project was cancelled 34 - No developer for requested skills

data.name: username
data.description: The username of the target user account
New oTasks can be created using the API, when you create a new oTask you need to define a code, description and URL
data.name: Create an oTask record
code
data.description: A task tracking code (This defines the task tracking code)

data.name: description
data.description: The code's description (This should be a description about the code being added)

data.name: url
data.description: The location where more info on the code can be found (The URL can be used to direct the user to more info about the code being entered)

data.name: username
data.description: The username of the target user account
Deletes all tasks within a company, team or assigned to a specific user.
data.name: Delete All oTask records
username
data.description: The username of the target user account
oTasks can be deleted using the API.
data.name: Delete an oTask record
format
data.description: note: format must be specified in tqx parameter, see example.

data.name: tq
data.value: SELECT worked_on, provider_id, provider_name, sum(hours) WHERE worked_on >= '2009-10-01' AND worked_on <= '2009-10-31'

data.description: Time reports can be generated for a specific team, with or without detailed monetary information based on the relationship of the authorized user at the time the call is made and what information is included in the call.
data.name: Generate Time Reports for a Specific Team
format
data.description: note: format must be specified in tqx parameter, see example

data.name: tq
data.value: SELECT week_worked_on, assignment_team_id, provider_id, assignment_name, sum(hours), sum(earnings) WHERE worked_on > '2009-10-01' AND worked_on <= '2009-10-31

data.description: Time reports can be generated for an agency, in order to use this API the authorized user needs staffing manager permissions to the agency.
data.name: Generating Agency Specific Reports
format
data.description: note: format must be specified in tqx parameter, see example

data.name: tq
data.value: SELECT week_worked_on, assignment_team_id, sum(hours), sum(charges) WHERE worked_on > '2009-10-01' AND worked_on <= '2009-10-31'

data.description: Time reports can be generated on a company-wide level. All time reports fields are supported on this level except earnings related fields. In order to access this API the authorized user needs either hiring or finance permissions to all teams within the company.
data.name: Generating Company Wide Reports
format
data.description: note: format must be specified in tqx parameter, see example

data.name: tq
data.value: SELECT worked_on, assignment_team_id, hours, task, memo WHERE worked_on > '2009-10-01' AND worked_on <= '2009-10-31'

data.description: This API allows callers to fetch data source of themselves. No monetary fields, such as charges or earnings, are supported. The caller of this API must be the provider himself.
data.name: Generating Provider Specific Reports
code1;code2;...;codeN
data.description: The specific task codes, the list of codes should be separated with ";"

data.name: username
data.description: The username of the target user account
return details on a specific oTask or set of oTasks, this format can be used within a company (:companyid), team (:teamid) or user (:userid)
data.name: Get a specific task record
job_key
data.description: The job key or a list of keys, separated by ";", number of keys per request is limited by 20. You can access profile by job recno, in that case you can't specify a list of jobs, only one profile per request is available.
